content:
Hi,

I was doing calls to NV, for spanish voters, and the callbank tool stopped working all of the sudden with "network connection lost" error. I have tried hitting retry with no luck. My internet connection is working find otherwise.

Has anybody else experienced this?

Thanks!
We have a brief tech issue.  Refresh and it should be working!
It looks like it is back! Thanks a lot, Denise!
yay! Glad to have you here.
Unfortunately, it looks like the technical issues are happening again...
hang in there, we just had another glitch.  I will be resolved quick.  hang out in <#1242256751445934262>  and we'll keep you updated!
yup, I just got kicked off, was in the middle of a call with a voter!
Will do. I will hang out in # calls-team!
And we are back... üôÇ
woo hoo!
connection just dropped again, I don't think it's a good experience for these people to be talking with us and the call to drop!
voter wanted to received the iwillvote text message link and I am not able to send
not ideal.  Hang in with us. We'll get it fixed!
could you help me to make sure this voter gets the link?
do you have their info?  You can put it in the debrief form.
I remember here full name, but didn't get the phone number
I navigated away from the screen trying to refresh
her*
where/what is the debrief form?
Ok, whatever you remember record here  [debrief form](https://forms.gle/JxfH2cGRx1Zrxty66)
ty
the dialer still doesn't seem to be working, I'm going to switch over to VoteForward letters
Stay on here, I'll let you know when we are back up. I just got in but not sure if its live.
üëç
I'm getting this message too trying to call NC
Please hop on the 8pm ZPB and you can get started there: https://txt.democrats.org/HPB/
